The Term ''East Overshoe'' is an [[Americanism (general)|americanism]] that is often used to refer to a place moderately far away. It generally is used in place of a city or town name when that name is unknown or cannot be recalled.
For example:
"I don't get to see Jim much since he moved. Now he lives somewhere out in East Overshoe."

Another usage is as a placeholder, representing a ficticious [[municipality]] in sample documents or hypothetical situations. This usage is similar to the way [[John Doe]] is sometimes used as a placeholder for the name of a person.